The paper focuses on representation learning over graph structured data using a novel hierarchical variational model and a semi-implicit variational inference method. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves probabilistic modeling (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) also suggests a potential fit with the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with dynamic graphs and link prediction, which could be relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SD) sub-category.
